OL,6,FIn the report, Mr Boutcher said
OL,7,F"various myths and erroneous stories"
OL,8,Fhave built up around Stakeknife.
OL,10,FHe said those within the security
OL,11,Fforces are defensive about the agent,
OL,12,Fviewing through "rose tinted
OL,13,Fspectacles" and claiming Stakeknife
OL,14,Fpotentially saved "hundreds of lives"
OL,15,Fwhile people outside the establishment
OL,16,Foverestimate the number of crimes the
OL,17,Fagent was responsible for.
OL,19,FMr Boutcher said the suggestion
OL,20,FStakeknife saved countless lives was
OL,21,Fnot grounded in fact.
