OL,6,F"I note the recent decisions made by
OL,7,Fthe Public Prosecution Service for
OL,8,FNorthern Ireland in relation to files
OL,9,Fpassed to them by Operation Kenova,
OL,10,Fwhich once again go to show how
OL,11,Fdifficult it is to achieve criminal
OL,12,Fjustice outcomes in legacy cases. Due
OL,13,Fto numerous related civil cases,
OL,14,Fhowever, that remain ongoing, it would
OL,15,Fbe inappropriate to comment further at
OL,16,Fthis time. There is also the prospect
OL,17,Fof appeals against any of the recent
OL,18,Fdecisions made by the Director for
OL,19,FPublic Prosecutions for Northern
OL,20,FIreland.
